<li>Green burial options</li>
<li>Pet memorial services</li>
<li>Monument and headstone assistance</li>
<li>Transportation and repatriation services</li>
</ul>
<p>Each service listing gives Google another signal about what your funeral home offers. Families searching for "cremation services near me" need to see cremation listed explicitly on your profile.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="Google Business Profile optimization checklist for funeral homes" src="/images/blog/funeral-home-gbp-checklist.webp" /></p>
<h3>Post Photos That Build Trust</h3>
<p>Funeral home photos serve a different purpose than most businesses. Families want to see your facility and feel reassured that their loved one will receive dignified care.</p>
<p>Post 3 to 5 photos per week:</p>
<ul>
<li>Your facility exterior and interior (clean, welcoming, professional)</li>
<li>Chapel and ceremony spaces</li>
<li>Staff in professional attire</li>
<li>Flower arrangements and memorial displays</li>
<li>Community involvement and events</li>
<li>Before-and-after facility improvements</li>
</ul>
<p>Avoid stock photos. Families can tell. Real photos of your actual facility build trust far more than generic imagery.</p>
