<h2>Content Strategy for Funeral Homes</h2>
<p>Most funeral home websites have 3 to 5 pages. A homepage, an about page, a services page, and a contact page. That is not enough for Google to rank you.</p>
<p>The funeral homes that dominate local search publish helpful, compassionate content consistently. Not salesy blog posts. Genuinely useful information for families during their most difficult moments.</p>
<h3>Content Categories That Work</h3>
<p><strong>Pre-planning guides.</strong> "How to Pre-Plan a Funeral: 7 Steps" or "Pre-Planning Checklist for Families." Pre-planning content attracts families months or years before they need services. When the time comes, they already trust you.</p>
<p><strong>Service explanations.</strong> "What Is a Celebration of Life?" or "Direct Cremation vs Traditional Cremation: Key Differences." These pages answer the questions families ask when making arrangements. Each service page targets a specific keyword and captures searchers with that exact intent.</p>
<p><strong>Cost and pricing guides.</strong> "How Much Does a Funeral Cost in [City]?" or "Understanding Cremation Pricing." Pricing transparency builds trust. Families appreciate funeral homes that address costs openly instead of hiding them behind a phone call.</p>
<p><strong>Grief support resources.</strong> "Coping With Loss: A Guide for Families" or "Grief Support Groups in [City]." Grief content serves families after services. It also signals to Google that your website is a trusted resource in your community.</p>
<p><strong>Obituary and memorial guides.</strong> "How to Write an Obituary: A Step-by-Step Guide" or "What to Include in a Memorial Program." These practical guides attract high search volume and position your funeral home as helpful and experienced.</p>
<p><strong>Local community content.</strong> "Memorial Day Events in [City]" or "Veterans Memorial Services in [Area]." Local content captures geographic searches and builds community connections.</p>
<h3>Publishing Frequency</h3>
<p>Consistency matters more than volume. Publishing 4 to 8 articles per month builds enough momentum to outrank competitors who publish nothing.</p>
<p>Research from <a href="https://blog.hubspot.com/marketing/blogging-frequency">HubSpot</a> shows businesses publishing 16+ posts per month get 3.5x more traffic than those publishing 0 to 4. For funeral homes, even 8 posts per month creates a significant competitive advantage.</p>
<p>For help building your publishing schedule, read our guide on <a href="/blog/create-content-calendar-seo/">creating a content calendar for SEO</a>.</p>
