<p>A funeral home with 200 reviews and a 4.8-star rating will outrank a competitor with 15 reviews and a 5.0-star rating. Volume and recency matter more than a perfect score.</p>
<h3>How to Build Your Review System</h3>
<p>Asking for reviews in the funeral industry requires sensitivity. But families who received excellent care are often willing to share their experience.</p>
<ol>
<li>Wait 2 to 3 weeks after services before requesting a review. Do not ask at the time of service.</li>
<li>Send a gentle email or handwritten note with a direct Google review link.</li>
<li>Place a subtle QR code on your thank-you cards and follow-up materials.</li>
<li>Respond to every review within 48 hours. Thank families by name. Address any concerns privately and professionally.</li>
</ol>
<p>Never incentivize reviews. Never pressure grieving families. The best approach is simply delivering excellent service and making it easy to share the experience.</p>
