<h2>Technical SEO for Funeral Home Websites</h2>
<p>A professional-looking website means nothing if Google cannot crawl and index it properly. Technical SEO ensures your site loads fast, works on mobile, and gives Google the right signals.</p>
<h3>Mobile-First Design</h3>
<p>Over 60% of funeral service searches happen on mobile devices. Families search from hospitals, care facilities, and their phones at home. Google uses mobile-first indexing. If your site does not work well on a phone, you will not rank.</p>
<p>Check these items:</p>
<ul>
<li>[ ] Pages load in under 2.5 seconds on mobile</li>
<li>[ ] Text is readable without zooming or pinching</li>
<li>[ ] Phone number is clickable (tap-to-call)</li>
<li>[ ] Contact forms work on mobile screens</li>
<li>[ ] Address links to Google Maps for directions</li>
</ul>
<h3>Schema Markup</h3>
<p>Schema markup tells Google exactly what your business is. For funeral homes, use the <code>FuneralHome</code> schema type (a subtype of <code>LocalBusiness</code>).</p>
<p>At minimum, add schema for:</p>
<ul>
<li>Business name, address, and phone number</li>
<li>Hours of operation (include 24/7 availability)</li>
<li>Services offered with descriptions</li>
<li>Reviews and aggregate ratings</li>
<li>Geographic service area</li>
</ul>
<p>For implementation help, read our <a href="/blog/schema-markup-seo-guide/">schema markup SEO guide</a>. Use our free <a href="/tools/schema-markup-generator/">schema markup generator</a> to create the JSON-LD code.</p>
<h3>Page Speed</h3>
<p>Slow websites lose visitors. Google research shows pages loading in over 3 seconds see a 53% higher bounce rate. For a family in immediate need, a slow website means they press the back button and call someone else.</p>
<p>Quick improvements:</p>
<ul>
<li>Compress all facility and service photos</li>
<li>Use WebP image format instead of PNG or JPEG</li>
<li>Enable browser caching</li>
<li>Remove unused plugins and scripts</li>
<li>Use a content delivery network for faster loading</li>
</ul>
<p>Run our free <a href="/tools/seo-audit/">SEO audit tool</a> to identify technical issues on your site.</p>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="Technical SEO checklist for funeral home websites" src="/images/blog/funeral-home-technical-seo.webp" /></p>
