<li>Dignity Memorial</li>
<li>Legacy.com</li>
<li>Funerals.org</li>
<li>Better Business Bureau</li>
<li>National Funeral Directors Association</li>
<li>State funeral directors association</li>
<li>Local Chamber of Commerce</li>
</ul>
<p>Consistency is critical. Your name, address, and phone number must match exactly across every listing. One inconsistency can confuse Google and hurt your rankings.</p>
<h3>Local Backlinks</h3>
<p>Target backlinks from organizations in your community.</p>
<ul>
<li><strong>Hospice and palliative care providers.</strong> Many list partner funeral homes on their website.</li>
<li><strong>Local churches and religious organizations.</strong> Offer to be listed as a recommended funeral home.</li>
<li><strong>Veterans organizations.</strong> If you offer military honors, connect with local VFW and American Legion posts.</li>
<li><strong>Hospital and care facility websites.</strong> Some list local funeral service providers for families.</li>
<li><strong>Community foundations and nonprofits.</strong> Sponsor local events and get listed on their sites.</li>
<li><strong>Local newspapers.</strong> Obituary sections often link to the funeral home handling services.</li>
</ul>
<p><img loading="lazy" alt="Funeral home citation and backlink sources for local SEO" src="/images/blog/funeral-home-backlink-sources.webp" /></p>
